## Type versus attribute

The core distinction. A type classifies the nature of the incident. An attribute describes a characteristic of it.

- **Working test (draft).** If removing the value would change what kind of incident it is, it is a type. If removing it would only remove detail about an otherwise-unchanged incident, it is an attribute.
